BIOSKETCH

   Stanislav Rada is a young researcher concerned with insect ecology and
   conservation, particularly in grasslands. This paper resulted from the
   research fellowship in Helmholtz Centre for Environmental Research.
   Here, the main author happily worked within the team focused on (apart
   from other topics) distribution, ecology and conservation of
   butterflies and other pollinators, impacts of land use and climate
   change on (insect) communities or biodiversity structure and dynamics.

   Author contributions: SR, TK, JS, MM and OS conceived the ideas. EK and
   AH compiled the data. SR and OS performed the analysis. SR and MM led
   the writing of the manuscript, with major contribution of OS and minor
   contributions of all other authors.

